eview mode)\n  -h, --help                 help for consensus\n      --mode string          Mode: code-review or general-prompt (required)\n      --plan-file string     Path to implementation plan file\n      --prompt string        Question to analyze (general-prompt mode)\n      --stage1-timeout int   Stage 1 timeout in seconds\n      --stage2-timeout int   Stage 2 timeout in seconds\n\nno agents available (need at least 1 API key)"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015VMUUu9dQobU1SnGjSWAjU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consensus is unavailable (no API keys configured). I'll proceed with autopilot mode, making design decisions based on my own analysis.\n\nLet me work through the key design decisions and document the design:\n\n**Q1: OT Model?**\n→ Choosing: **Simple character-based OT with insert/delete operations**\nReasoning: Simplest to implement correctly, well-understood transformation functions, fits the server-mediated architecture where the server is the single source of truth. CRDTs add complexity without benefit when we have a central server.\n\n**Q2: Architecture pattern?**\n→ Choosing: **Server-as-authority with sequential version numbering**\nReasoning: Server assigns version numbers, clients send operations against a known version, server transforms against any intervening operations. Simple, proven, and SQLite's single-writer model naturally serializes operations.\n\n**Q3: WebSocket message protocol?**\n→ Choosing: **JSON messages with type discriminator**\nReasoning: Simple, debuggable, sufficient performance for text editing.\n\n**Q4: Project structure?**\n→ Choosing: **Modular single-package with separate files for db, ot, routes, websocket**\nReasoning: Clean separation without over-engineering.\n\nLet me write the design document."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":656,"cache_read_input_tokens":23180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":656},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"274107e4-c876-42cb-bfc4-47a85a37deab","uuid":"ca43230a-e6f5-4ccf-bd11-9fb540a8e0bb"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015VMUUu9dQobU1SnGjSWAjU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SU59E34AQ85D7SPUVATTd7","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-collab-editor-design.md","content":"# Collaborative Document Editor - Design\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nServer-as-authority model. The server maintains the canonical document state and version number. Clients send operations referencing their known version; the server transforms them against any concurrent operations, applies them, increments the version, persists, and broadcasts.\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n  server.ts        - createApp factory, Express + WS setup\n  db.ts            - SQLite schema, document & version CRUD\n  ot.ts            - OT types, transform functions, apply/compose\n  routes.ts        - REST API routes for document management\n  websocket.ts     - WebSocket connection handler, room management\n```\n\n## OT Model\n\nTwo operation types:\n- `insert(position, text)` - insert text at character position\n- `delete(position, count)` - delete count characters starting at position\n\nOperations are individual (not compound/sequences). Each operation references the document version it was created against.\n\nTransform function `transform(opA, opB)` → `[opA', opB']` such that applying opA then opB' yields the same result as applying opB then opA'.\n\nServer workflow:\n1. Receive operation from client with `baseVersion`\n2. Fetch all operations from `baseVersion` to current version\n3. Transform incoming op against each stored op sequentially\n4. Apply transformed op to document content\n5. Store operation with new version number\n6. Broadcast transformed op to all other clients with new version\n\n## Database Schema\n\n**documents** table:\n- id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY, UUID)\n- title (TEXT)\n- content (TEXT, current document state)\n- version (INTEGER, current version number)\n- created_at (TEXT, ISO timestamp)\n- updated_at (TEXT, ISO timestamp)\n\n**operations** table:\n- id (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)\n- document_id (TEXT, FK)\n- version (INTEGER, version this op produced)\n- type (TEXT, 'insert' or 'delete')\n- position (INTEGER)\n- text (TEXT, for inserts)\n- count (INTEGER, for deletes)\n- client_id (TEXT)\n- created_at (TEXT)\n\nIndex on (document_id, version).\n\n## REST API\n\n- `POST /documents` - Create document (title, optional content)\n- `GET /documents` - List all documents\n- `GET /documents/:id` - Get document with current content\n- `PUT /documents/:id` - Update document title/content directly\n- `DELETE /documents/:id` - Delete document\n- `GET /documents/:id/history` - Get version history (list of operations)\n\n## WebSocket Protocol\n\nConnect to `/ws/:documentId?clientId=xxx`\n\n### Messages (Server → Client)\n- `{ type: \"sync\", content, version, documentId }` - Initial sync on connect\n- `{ type: \"operation\", op: {...}, version }` - Broadcast transformed operation\n- `{ type: \"ack\", version }` - Acknowledge client's operation was applied\n- `{ type: \"error\", message }` - Error message\n\n### Messages (Client → Server)\n- `{ type: \"operation\", op: { type: \"insert\"|\"delete\", position, text?, count? }, baseVersion }` - Submit an edit\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- Invalid JSON → error message to client\n- Missing fields → error message to client\n- Invalid position (out of bounds) → error message to client\n- Document not found → error message / 404\n- Server never crashes on bad input\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit tests for OT transform functions (core correctness)\n- Integration tests for REST API (CRUD lifecycle)\n- Integration tests for WebSocket (connect, edit, broadcast)\n- Concurrency test: multiple clients editing simultaneously, verify convergence\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":656,"cache_read_