+# Collaborative Document Editor - Design
+
+## Architecture Overview
+
+Server-as-authority model. The server maintains the canonical document state and version number. Clients send operations referencing their known version; the server transforms them against any concurrent operations, applies them, increments the version, persists, and broadcasts.
+
+## Project Structure
+
+```
+src/
+  server.ts        - createApp factory, Express + WS setup
+  db.ts            - SQLite schema, document & version CRUD
+  ot.ts            - OT types, transform functions, apply/compose
+  routes.ts        - REST API routes for document management
+  websocket.ts     - WebSocket connection handler, room management
+```
+
+## OT Model
+
+Two operation types:
+- `insert(position, text)` - insert text at character position
+- `delete(position, count)` - delete count characters starting at position
+
+Operations are individual (not compound/sequences). Each operation references the document version it was created against.
+
+Transform function `transform(opA, opB)` → `[opA', opB']` such that applying opA then opB' yields the same result as applying opB then opA'.
+
+Server workflow:
+1. Receive operation from client with `baseVersion`
+2. Fetch all operations from `baseVersion` to current version
+3. Transform incoming op against each stored op sequentially
+4. Apply transformed op to document content
+5. Store operation with new version number
+6. Broadcast transformed op to all other clients with new version
+
+## Database Schema
+
+**documents** table:
+- id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY, UUID)
+- title (TEXT)
+- content (TEXT, current document state)
+- version (INTEGER, current version number)
+- created_at (TEXT, ISO timestamp)
+- updated_at (TEXT, ISO timestamp)
+
+**operations** table:
+- id (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)
+- document_id (TEXT, FK)
+- version (INTEGER, version this op produced)
+- type (TEXT, 'insert' or 'delete')
+- position (INTEGER)
+- text (TEXT, for inserts)
+- count (INTEGER, for deletes)
+- client_id (TEXT)
+- created_at (TEXT)
+
+Index on (document_id, version).
+
+## REST API
+
+- `POST /documents` - Create document (title, optional content)
+- `GET /documents` - List all documents
+- `GET /documents/:id` - Get document with current content
+- `PUT /documents/:id` - Update document title/content directly
+- `DELETE /documents/:id` - Delete document
+- `GET /documents/:id/history` - Get version history (list of operations)
+
+## WebSocket Protocol
+
+Connect to `/ws/:documentId?clientId=xxx`
+
+### Messages (Server → Client)
+- `{ type: "sync", content, version, documentId }` - Initial sync on connect
+- `{ type: "operation", op: {...}, version }` - Broadcast transformed operation
+- `{ type: "ack", version }` - Acknowledge client's operation was applied
+- `{ type: "error", message }` - Error message
+
+### Messages (Client → Server)
+- `{ type: "operation", op: { type: "insert"|"delete", position, text?, count? }, baseVersion }` - Submit an edit
+
+## Error Handling
+
+- Invalid JSON → error message to client
+- Missing fields → error message to client
+- Invalid position (out of bounds) → error message to client
+- Document not found → error message / 404
+- Server never crashes on bad input
+
+## Testing Strategy
+
+- Unit tests for OT transform functions (core correctness)
+- Integration tests for REST API (CRUD lifecycle)
+- Integration tests for WebSocket (connect, edit, broadcast)
+- Concurrency test: multiple clients editing simultaneously, verify convergence
